-- Italy's 10-year bond yield hits new low, dips below 2 pct  
-- By Irene Chappisi
-- Wed Dec 03, 2014 04:19AM EST
-- None



MILAN, Dec 3 (Reuters) - The yield on Italy's 10-year government bond hit a new record low since the launch of the euro, falling below 2 percent, with sentiment boosted by expectations the European Central Bank will launch a bond-buying programme to boost the euro zone economy.

